SIMPLE: pluff
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pluff
<hw>Pluff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Prob. of imitative
origin.]</ety> <def>To throw out, as smoke, dust, etc., in puffs.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluff</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pluff
<hw>Pluff</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A puff, as of smoke from
a pipe, or of dust from a puffball; a slight explosion, as of a small
quantity of gunpowder.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hairdresser's powder puff; also, the act of using
it.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plug</ent>⟦br⟧
